# Verification and release safety

- Run the fastest relevant deterministic checks before broader browser or visual review.
- Use only scripts that exist in `package.json`; propose missing checks instead of inventing passing results.
- Do not disable TypeScript, lint, build, accessibility, privacy, analytics, or performance checks.
- Never delete or mass-update expected results solely to make a failure disappear.
- Validate preview behavior before requesting production approval.
- Production deployment, rollback, environment variables, and branch protection remain human-controlled.
- Report failed checks and pre-existing failures separately from failures introduced by the change.
- Include a rollback note when changing routing, analytics, consent, or deployment configuration.
